title: SRAM Tour of the Gila Fun Ride
Pajarito Punishment-Downhill

address.street: 397 Camp May Road, Los Alamos, NM 87544

description: Pajarito Mountain Ski Area is proud to host this year\'s Southwest Gravity Series Pajarito Punishment Downhill Race! This spectator-friendly race will surely challenge you to your limits. It is fast, it\'s steep, and it\'s technical, and we know you will enjoy the ride! If the altitude doesn\'t take your breath away the amazing views around the trails of Pajarito and the National Forrest will. So bring your friends, bring your bike and bring your A game, and join us for this year\'s best event in the area!
course: The downhill race course will be the race trail designed by Chris Boice (Yetti National Team) & Rich Strang (Godfather of NM freeriding) that was used for the 2009-2011 races.  See \"Downhill Racecourse\" on Pajarito Bike Map.
registration: There are four different categories that are sub-divided by age, and the entry fees differ accordingly.  On race day, age groups within each category may be combined depending on how many entries there are for each age.  The entry fee includes a T-shirt (T-shirt only guaranteed if pre-registered online), Sunday\'s Lift Ticket and entrance into the race.  Saturday\'s practice will also require an onsite purchase of a discounted $15 day pass.  Cat 1 and Pro riders must have current USA Cycling license.  Cat 2 and Cat 3 riders may purchase $5 one-day license for the event. Pre reg is highly encouraged and can be done by clicking here; https://www.usacycling.org/myusac/index.php?pagename=registration&eventid=2180&year=2012
notes: The race format will be a \"best of two\" run format just like previous years.

title: MSC #2, Chile Challenge
description:
MSC #2, Chile Challenge is a part of the Mountain States Cup (MSC)--the largest full-discipline (endurance and gravity) race series in the United States.

Saturday\'s events include a cross country race and super d. The cross country consists of 8-mile laps with lots of climbing and is a true mountian biker\'s course that\'ll call on every skill you have as a rider. The guys and girls with the best all-around game are going to find themselves on the podium.

Sunday\'s events include a downhill race. Angel Fire is world renown for its downhill courses. We will have two separate course- one for Pro\'s and one for all other courses. The Super D is also heavy on the D.

Cross country and downhill are qualifiers for the 2012 USA Cycling Mountain Bike National Championships.

All racers 18 & under pay the junior entry fee. So even if you race CAT 1 15-18, make sure to register under the Junior category so you receive the best price!
course: Visit http://www.racemsc.com/schedule/chilechallenge.html for all course maps and descriptions.
notes: Visit http://www.racemsc.com/schedule/chilechallenge.html for all updated race information.
directions:
Angel Fire by Car
Angel Fire Resort is a scenic drive from most major cities in Texas, Oklahoma, Kansas, Colorado, Arizona and New Mexico. For detailed directions, go to www.mapquest.com. 

Current Road Conditions
New Mexico
www.nmroads.com
Roads Advisory Hotline: 800-432-4269

Angel Fire by Air
You can fly into Albuquerque Sunport International Airport from just about anywhere. From Albuquerque, a beautiful 3-hour drive takes you through Northern New Mexico to Angel Fire.

title: Signal Peak Challenge
description:
Signal Peak Challenge:  Apocalypse Cow
Cross-Country Mountain Bike Race
Part of the NMORS http://nmcycling.org/NMBRA/NMORS_2012.html
course: Back to the \"old courses\".  Cat 1 does a big 22 mi. loop and another 8 mi. loop.  Cat 2 does a big loop, and Cat 3 does 5.5 mile loops.
registration:
Sign up online at www.usacycling.org before noon on Friday, August 5th, 2012 for $30 plus fees.  Registration also at Gila Hike & Bike until Saturday 8/11 ($35).  T shirts $12 extra. You must pay for shirts before 8/1/12 to order the right size.  

On-site Registration ($35) and Number Pick-up:  Sunday 8/12 at Start/Finish Line 7:15 a.m.-8:15 a.m.
notes: Race fee buys a plate at the BBQ dinner on Saturday, 7:00 p.m. at the staging area. No refunds, no rain date.  Course will be flagged on Saturday afternoon, 8/11/12, for pre-riding.
directions: To get to the Start/Finish, head north from Silver City on NM HWY 15 for 14.5 miles (towards Gila Cliff Dwellings), turn right on onto Signal Peak Road (FR 154) and the staging area will be on your left in 100 yards. Parking will be off of Signal Peak Road, please park in pullouts to ease congestion, and there will be No-Parking zones marked off. Do Not Park on the pavement of NM 15, please.

title: Road Apple Rally
description: The Road Apple Rally is the oldest Continuously Run Mountain Bike Race in the  United States
course:
This course is a 15 or 30 mile loop starting and finishing at Lions Wilderness Park Amphitheater.  The amphitheater can be reached by turning north at the junction of Pinon Hills Blvd. and College Blvd. and following the signs to the amphitheater.
The majority of the course is single track joined with sections of dirt and paved roads.  ALL CATEGORY 3  (Beginners) WILL RIDE THE SHORT LOOP APPROXIMATELY 15 MILES, AND ALL OTHERS WILL RIDE THE LONG COURSE, APPROXIMATELY 30 MILES.
registration:
Pre-registration must be received by October 4, 2012.  Mail in registration should be mailed to Road Apple Rally, 901 Fairgrounds Rd., Farmington, New Mexico 87401.  Race and includes T-shirt and lunch.  All entrants in the cross-country race will be required to show proof of USA Cycling license at packet pickup.
LATE REGISTRATION
There is NO RACE DAY REGISTRATION.   Participants registering for the race will have to pay a $15.00 late fee to register in person on October 5, 2012
No faxed or scanned entries will be accepted.
Online registration closes at 11:59 p.m. MDT on October 4, 2012.
